just_use cards.py

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: card primitives — the BFS planner's bottom layer

The Python equivalent of the Elm `Game.Rules.StackType` rule
predicates plus the constants and small helpers that go with
the agent-side card model.

## Status

- **Mirrors:** `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Rules/StackType.elm`
  (`isLegalStack` / `isPartialOk` / `neighbors`) + bits of
  `Game.Rules.Card.elm`. (Predicates moved out of
  `Game.Agent.Cards` into Rules/ on 2026-04-28.)
- **Origin:** lifted out of the now-retired `beginner.py`
  on 2026-04-26 as the module split landed; the IDDFS
  planner cluster (`beginner` / `run_corpus_v2` /
  `beginner_corpus`) was purged 2026-04-27. These
  primitives now live here as the BFS planner's bottom
  layer.

## What it owns

- **Card model:** `RANKS`, `SUITS`, `RED` constants;
  `card(label, deck)` parser; `label`, `label_d` renderers;
  `succ`, `color` value helpers.
- **Classification:** `classify(stack)` (the hottest
  function in the search), `partial_ok(stack)`.
- **Neighborhood:** `neighbors(c)` — every shape that could
  sit adjacent to a card in some legal group.
- **Verb eligibility:** `can_peel_kind`, `can_pluck_kind`,
  `can_yank_kind`, `can_steal_kind`, `can_split_out_kind`.
  Mirror the Elm `canPeel` / `canPluck` / etc. inside
  `Enumerator.elm`.

## What it doesn't own

- Stack geometry (location, board layout): not part of the
  agent's view; lives in `Game.CardStack` (Go) +
  `Game.BoardGeometry` (Elm).
- Trick / hint logic: that's `strategy.py` (legacy) +
  not-yet-ported in Elm.
- Stack-display rendering: `show_board.py` carries its own
  `_label` helper for one-stack-per-line dict output (server
  state shape). Not load-bearing for the planner.

## Pointers

- Elm sibling: `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Rules/StackType.elm`
  + `Game.Rules.Card.elm`.
- Tests: card primitives are exercised indirectly through
  `test_bfs_extract.py`, `test_bfs_enumerate.py`.
